headline: Mag 7 plus Oracle equals GAMMATON! Strategist talks tech acronym.
summary: What do you get when you add one more Big Tech stock to the Magnificent Seven? The answer is GAMMATON! Interactive Brokers chief strategist Steve Sosnick explains his newest acronym for prospective AI and tech picks, GAMMATON, which consists of Alphabet (GOOGL, GOOG), Apple (AAPL), Microsoft (MSFT), Meta Platforms (META), Amazon (AMZN), Tesla (TSLA), Oracle (ORCL), and Nvidia (NVDA). Also hear Steve Sosnick elaborate on whether AI investors should pivot from Nvidia (NVDA) into Oracle after the latter's colossal stock gain this week. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.

headline: Should Investors Rethink IBM After Quantum Computing Breakthrough and Recent Price Gains?
summary: Thinking about what to do with International Business Machines stock right now? You are not alone. With shares of IBM up a solid 2.0% in just the past week and delivering an impressive 168.2% return over five years, investors are rightfully taking a closer look. The momentum is not just a short-term story either, as the stock has climbed 15.2% year-to-date and is up 21.3% over the past twelve months. headline: A Fresh Look at Google's (GOOGL) Valuation Following Court Ruling That Removes Breakup Risk
summary: The recent U.S. District Court decision was the kind of event Alphabet (GOOGL) shareholders have been watching closely for months. By ruling in favor of the company and confirming it can maintain control of core products like Chrome and Android, the court effectively swept away one of the biggest clouds hanging over the stock. Investors saw this as a green light to return, with concerns about a forced breakup now off the table and Alphabet’s competitive position reaffirmed for the foreseeable...

headline: How Mastercard’s (MA) AI-Powered Payments Push and Tech Partnerships Have Changed Its Investment Story
summary: In the past week, Mastercard announced a suite of AI-powered payment products and developer tools, expanded consulting services, and new collaborations with global technology leaders such as Stripe, Google, and Ant International, supporting a rollout of its Agent Pay program to all U.S. cardholders by the end of the holiday season. This initiative positions Mastercard at the forefront of advancing secure, intelligent commerce by making AI-enabled payments and agentic capabilities accessible...
